To whom it may reach to...

I am a upcoming padel player who has been playing padel for over 3years. I have expanded my interest to grow due to the knowledge ive grown over the years and the improvement. I have tested myself in high level and confirmed that im ready to take on a new journey on becoming amongst the greatest. It's not a easy journey but I believe I can someone worth investing in the future when given a chance. Hoping not to only showcase my skills and talent on the courts but also to grow my padel knowledge outside the court to grow and expand my experience in home country for development. 

I thank you for reading my message. I look forward to hear from you.

IG:@Padel_Guy
sponsors: Eden Padel, FilaPadel.sa, Padelthat.com and Jubeelo Padel.

short_bio:
I’ve been playing Padel for a little while over 2 years now and I truly can’t get enough of the sport, I’ve grown to have a strong passion and love for the sport and continue to try and grow and pursue my career in the sport as best I can. 
Currently I’m a club ambassador for 10by20 Padel club lenasia and I’ve managed to gain a good following and a good few wins over the time I’ve been playing, as well as competing in high level and advanced tournaments along with some of the best players in the country. 
I’m Hoping to continue my journey and try to make it as far as I can, hopefully becoming one of the high ranked/top Padel players in the country.
sponsors: Diadora South Africa - Ambassador for 10by20 Padel Club (Lenasia) /

short_bio: Padel and tennis are my lifelong passions, backed by over six years of tennis coaching experience across Levels 1–3, including roles at Ivan Sequiera Tennis Academy and V-Tennis in London. After returning to South Africa in 2011 and successfully running two PostNet franchise stores for 13 years, I transitioned fully into Padel, earning my CAP qualification in 2023. Since then, I’ve served as Head Coach at Top Padel and, in 2024, joined The Country Club Johannesburg—South Africa’s premier Padel venue with nine courts and 4,400 members. Known for strong social skills and expertise in biomechanics, I specialise in correcting technical errors and thrive in both team and independent environments.

short_bio: My name is Muhammad, and I started playing padel because I loved the speed and energy of the game. At first I was just trying it for fun, but the more I played, the more I realised how competitive I am. I’m known for fighting for every point, staying calm under pressure, and always trying to improve. Whether I’m smashing, volleying, or chasing down a tough ball, I give 100%. I’m still growing as a player, but every match teaches me something new. My goal is simple — keep getting better, play with heart, and enjoy every moment on the court.
